The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Feb. 6 (PTI): The disabled would not have to pay extra while travelling by air for facilities like wheelchair or ambulift when a new rule of the Directorate General of Civil Aviation (DGCA) becomes effective.           
	The DGCA has sought comments from airlines and airport operators and is likely to finalise it by nest month.                  
	 Mumbai: Mohammed Ajmal Kasabs DNA samples have matched those from the articles on the trawler he and nine other Mumbai gunmen used, police said today, days before Pakistan unveils the results of its probe.The Centre could use the trawler sample, another crucial piece of evidence, to corner Pakistan.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): A 150-year-old statue of St Xavier in front of a church was damaged in an attack yesterday, leading to tension in Kanyakumari district. A large police team has been deployed in Karungal, officials said. A case has been registered following a complaint from the church secretary. The police have ordered the statue shifted for forensic tests.                   
	 Amritsar (PTI): A Chinese man was arrested by the BSF for allegedly trying to cross over to Pakistan without valid documents on Thursday, officials said in Amritsar. Alimu Pilliwaldi was arrested at the Attari check post under the Indian Passport Act.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): At least four persons are feared killed in an avalanche in Kupwara district of Jammu and Kashmir, police said. The avalanche struck Z-Gali near Machil on the Line of Control on Friday.                  
	 Rameswaram (PTI): About 60 Indian fishermen were allegedly attacked by the Sri Lankan navy off the Ramanathpuram district on Friday. The fishermen alleged their fishing nets were damaged and their global positioning system equipment, distress call wireless sets and cellphones were seized.                                                                                                                           
